      • insert

        public void insert(java.lang.Object value,
                   int position)
        Inserts (does not overwrite) the given value at the given position in array ( before actual insertion elements at position and at greater positions will be shifted one place toward the end). The legal positions are 0 to size. Complexity of operation is O(n).
        Parameters:
        value - object to insert into array
        position - new position of an object from argument
        Throws:
        java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException - if requested position is less than zero or greater than size.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if object is null.
